Sentencas: Vaporization of the La0.85Sr0.15Ga0.85Mg0.15O2.85, and La0.90Sr0.10Ga0.80M0.20O2.85 perovskite phases was investigated by the use of Knudsen effusion mass spectrometry in the temperature range of 1618-1886 K.
Titulo: Vaporization of Sr- and Mg-doped lanthanum gallate and implications for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The partial pressures of the gaseous species O-2, Mg, Sr, SrO, Ga, GaO, Ga2O, and LaO were determined over the samples investigated.

Sentencas: The equilibrium partial pressures were used for the calculation of thermodynamic activities of the components at 1800 K.
Titulo: Vaporization of Sr- and Mg-doped lanthanum gallate and implications for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results are compared with thermodynamic data of LaGaO3(s) without additives.

Sentencas: Implications of the present data for the potential use of the material in solid oxide fuel cell technology are discussed as well.
